<p><b>Akrasia</b> (<a href="/wiki/Greek_language" title="Greek language">ancient Greek</a> <span lang="grc" xml:lang="grc">ἀκρασία</span>, "lacking command (over oneself)"), occasionally transliterated as <b>acrasia</b>, is the state of acting against one's better judgment.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
